                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d250">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Commandant <persName type="from">Newton</persName>, United
                        States Navy, to Master <persName type="to">Pearson</persName>, United States
                        Navy.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Sealed orders.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <dateline>
                    <date calendar="gregorian" when="1849-08-28">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">August</hi> 28, 1849</date>.</dateline>
                <p>
                    <seg type="margin">[699]</seg>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: You will proceed without delay to the southeast
                    end of Horn Island with the United States steamer General Taylor, under your
                    command, where you will find the sloop of war Albany, Commander V. M. Randolph,
                    to whom you will report.</p>
                <p>I have requested him to send you back with the General Taylor, at the expiration
                    of one week from the date on which you report, and sooner if your services can
                    be dispensed with.</p>
                <p>You will take every precaution to prevent accident by fire, or otherwise, and be
                    strictly governed by the rules and regulations which are hung up on board.</p>
                <p>I am, respectfully, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <list>
                            <item>JOHN THOMAS NEWTON,<lb/>
                                <hi rend="italic">Commandant.</hi>
                            </item>
                            <item>Mr. <hi rend="smallcaps">John Pearson</hi>,<lb/>
                                <hi rend="italic">Master United States Navy, Commanding Steamer
                                    General Taylor.</hi>
                            </item>
                        </list>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
